entry.tran: 不愿意的；不情愿的；不乐意的
entry.def: If you are unwilling to do something, you do not want to do it and will not agree to do it.

example.ex: Initially the government was unwilling to accept the defeat...
example.tran: 最初政府不愿意承认失败。

example.ex: For months I had been either unwilling or unable to go through with it.
example.tran: 数月来，我一直不是不愿意就是没办法做这件事。

entry.def: You can use unwilling to describe someone who does not really want to do the thing they are doing.

example.ex: A youthful teacher, he finds himself an unwilling participant in school politics...
example.tran: 作为一名年轻教师，他发现自己并不情愿地参与到了学校的权力争斗中。

example.ex: She was certainly an unwilling victim of circumstances.
example.tran: 她成为情势的牺牲品绝对不是自己愿意的。
